MARTIN et al. v. FREED. (Supreme Court, General Term, Second Department. May 14, 1894.) Action by George W. Martin and others against Samuel C. Freed.

Argued before BROWN, P. J., and DYKMAN and CULLEN, JJ.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs on opinion of Dykman, J., in Pitt v. Freed, 28 N. Y. Supp. 863.
